    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001893_0001.jpg" n="0001"/>

<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName><geogName type="river">River Shire</geogName></placeName> 
<lb/><date when="1863-02-25">25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> February 1863</date></dateline>
<lb/><salute>Sir</salute>,</opener>
<lb/><p><hi rend="center">Three <unclear cert="high">Black</unclear> men who were brought</hi>
<lb/>from the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName> by the late <persName><term type="occupation">Bishop</term> MacKenzie</persName> to
<lb/>assist the Universities Mission are now sent
<lb/>back to their homes. They were brought up the
<lb/><!-- I cannot make out this word. JM --> of the <term type="occupation">Admiral</term> in a man of war, and
<lb/>if you can give them a passage down I am <unclear cert="medium"><w>in-
<lb break="no"/>formed</w></unclear> by the missionaries to say that all expenses
<lb/>will cheerfully be paid to your <term type="occupation">Paymaster</term> by the
<lb/><term type="occupation">Bishop</term> of the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName>.</p>
<lb/><p>In introducing <unclear cert="low">them</unclear> it <!-- I cannot make out this word, or words. JM --> be right in
<lb/>me not to mention that but little can be said in
<lb/>favour of their moral characters &amp; behaviour
<lb/>while with the Mission.</p>
<lb/><p>Allow me to add, that as the <placeName><geogName type="river">Lower Shire</geogName></placeName>  
<lb/>has been completely <unclear cert="high">repopulated</unclear> with slave hunting
<lb/>drought, and famine, we can purchase no
<lb/>provisions for the Pioneer and will be
<lb/><hi rend="right"/>obliged
<lb/><hi rend="left"/>The <term type="occupation">Captain</term> of any Man of War
<lb/>touching <unclear cert="low">at</unclear> <placeName><country><choice><orig>Mosambique</orig><reg>Mozambique</reg></choice></country></placeName>
    
    <pb facs="liv_001893_0002.jpg" n="0002"/>
<lb/>obliged to return to the <placeName><settlement type="village">Kongone</settlement></placeName> - <placeName><settlement type="village">Quillimane</settlement></placeName> or
<lb/><placeName><country>Mozambique</country></placeName> for stores sooner than we anticipate, 
<lb/>if you can leave any forces at either of these
<lb/>Ports you will confer a very great favour
<lb/>and render us essential service <unclear cert="low">&amp;</unclear> as it will
<lb/>be unwise for us to venture to <placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> at
<lb/>this Season in this small craft <space extent="2" unit="chars"/> I have to
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">beg</unclear> very <unclear cert="medium">earnestly</unclear> that you will take this request
<lb/>into your favourable consideration.</p>
<lb/><p>The <placeName><geogName type="river">Shire</geogName></placeName> has not risen as much
<lb/>as usual this year, and we have found <w>con-
<lb break="no"/>siderable</w> difficulty in getting the two vessels
<lb/>up through the <term type="animal">Elephant</term> Swamp, but we
<lb/>hope soon to reach the Cataracts</p> <!-- I am not sure how to code "cataracts". JM -->
<lb/><p>Our <term type="occupation">Blacksmith</term> <persName>William Mcleod</persName> is
<lb/>obliged by <term type="ailment">disease of the kidneys</term> to leave us,
<lb/>he is a very good man, we got him from the 
<lb/><unclear cert="low">"Goryon"</unclear> on his passage to the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName>.</p>
<lb/><closer>I am <unclear cert="medium">&amp;c</unclear>
<lb/><!-- There is a symbol here which I cannot make out. JM -->
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed>
<lb/><hi rend="underline">H.M.S. Cowal</hi></closer>
    
            </div>
